name: KLM Boeing 777-200ER Close Up Taxi and Takeoff from Calgary Airport
description:
Back to some spotting content, otherwise known as my comfort zone in my corner of YouTube, lol. Back on January 5th, this KLM Triple Seven operated an extra flight as 'KLM 680' due to a sick crew member the previous day resulting in a cancellation.

It departed around 1400 local time, a bit after the regular Amsterdam flight arrived, so for a moment we had two KLM aircraft on the ground! 

Here we have one of KLM's Boeing 777-200ERs, taxiing up close on Bravo and departing runway 17L, with some fantastic sound from those GE90s. ATC is included!

Thanks for watching!
